            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-history"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} has no prior hospitalizations and no significant surgical history. She was diagnosed with mild anxiety disorder at age 33 and has been managing it with lifestyle measures and intermittent counselling, without pharmacological therapy. She has a documented history of iron-deficiency anaemia, diagnosed two years ago postpartum, for which she completed a course of oral iron supplementation; her most recent haemoglobin was within normal limits. She reports occasional tension-type headaches, managed with over-the-counter ibuprofen — a habit that may be contributing to her reflux symptoms given the gastroprotective concerns associated with NSAIDs. She has no history of peptic ulcer disease, Helicobacter pylori infection, or prior upper gastrointestinal investigations. She is nulliparous of further pregnancies, and her last cervical smear was normal 18 months ago. She takes no regular prescribed medications. Family history is notable for her mother having GORD and her paternal grandfather having had oesophageal cancer. {patientName} is a lifelong non-smoker, consumes alcohol socially (approximately 7–10 units per week), and drinks 3–4 cups of coffee daily. Her BMI is 27.1 kg/m². She has no known drug allergies on record prior to this visit."
          }
        ]
      }
    }
